final String PrivacyPolicysum ='''At MoneyWave, along with our subsidiaries and affiliates (referred to collectively as “MoneyWave,” “we,” “our,” or “us”), we are committed to safeguarding your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and share your information when you interact with us through our website, mobile applications, educational learning courses, and other services (collectively, the "Services"). We encourage you to review this policy regularly, as we may update it periodically. Any changes will be reflected in the "Last Updated" date at the end of this document.

### Information We Collect

*Information You Provide*
We collect information that you voluntarily share with us, which may occur when you create an account, participate in interactive features, engage in surveys or promotions, subscribe to newsletters, make purchases, enroll in our educational learning courses, refer others to our Services, apply for a job, connect with us on social media, request customer support, or otherwise communicate with us. This information may include your name, email address, username, password, mailing address, phone number, language preferences, and payment details (such as credit or debit card information). 

For users of our educational services, we may also collect details related to your course enrollments, progress, assessments, certificates earned, and feedback. Additionally, if you refer someone to our Services, we may collect information about them, such as their email address.

*Automatically Collected Information*
When you engage with our Services, we collect certain information automatically, including:
- *Log Data:* This includes information such as your IP address, web requests, access times, pages viewed, browser type, and the page you visited before accessing our Services. It may also include your activities on our educational platform, such as courses viewed or interacted with.
- *Device Data:* We collect information about the device you use to access our Services, including the model, operating system, unique identifiers, and network details. This helps us ensure device compatibility with course content and resolve technical issues.
- *Location Data:* If you use location-enabled features or consent to the collection of location data, we may gather information to recommend relevant content, such as courses tailored to your region. For more information on managing location data, see the "Your Choices" section below.
- *Cookies and Tracking Technologies:* We use cookies, small data files stored on your browser, to enhance your experience by tracking popular content and counting visits. We may also use web beacons, small graphics embedded in emails or web pages, to track user engagement and measure the effectiveness of our marketing efforts. For more details on managing cookies, see the "Your Choices" section below.

*Information from Other Sources*
We may also collect information from third-party sources and combine it with the data we gather through our Services. For example, if you log in through a social media account, we may access certain profile information as permitted by that platform. If you access our educational courses via a third-party platform, we may collect information about your participation and progress in those courses.

### How We Use Your Information

At MoneyWave, we do not sell your personal information. We use the information we collect for the following purposes:
- To provide, maintain, and improve our Services, including our educational learning courses.
- To fulfill your requests, process transactions, and send necessary information such as confirmations and invoices.
- To communicate with you regarding updates, security alerts, and other support-related messages, particularly about your account or course access.
- To respond to inquiries and provide customer support, especially for issues related to course access or completion.
- To inform you about products, services, promotions, and events that may be relevant to your interests, including educational content aligned with your preferences.
- To analyze trends and user behavior in order to improve our Services, including how users interact with our educational platform and course content.
- To personalize your experience by delivering content or advertisements that match your interests, such as tailored course recommendations based on your learning history or professional goals.
- To manage contests, promotions, and related rewards, especially those connected to our referral programs or educational courses.
- To conduct advertising and analytics activities, as described in the Advertising and Analytics section below.
- To integrate information from other sources in order to better understand your needs and improve our services.
- To use your information for any other purpose for which it was originally collected.

### Social Sharing Features

Our Services may include social sharing features, allowing you to share your activities on the platform (such as course progress or certificate completions) with other media or social platforms. The use of these features depends on the privacy settings you configure on our Services and those of the social platforms you use.

### Advertising and Analytics

We may allow third-party entities to deliver advertisements and provide analytics services. These entities may use cookies, web beacons, and similar technologies to collect data about your use of our Services and other websites. This information is used to analyze trends, track user behavior, and deliver personalized advertisements, including ads related to our educational courses.

We may collaborate with partners who collect, store, and share unique identifiers linked to your device, helping us deliver tailored ads while you browse online. These partners may also combine demographic data or other non-personally identifiable information you provide.

### Security Measures

We implement reasonable security practices to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. This includes the protection of data related to your participation in our educational courses, ensuring confidentiality and security of your learning records.

### Your Choices

*Account Information*
You can update, correct, or delete your account information by logging into your account or contacting us directly. If you wish to deactivate your account, please reach out to us. While we may retain certain information as required by law or for legitimate business purposes, cached or archived copies of your data may be retained temporarily.

*Device and Location Settings*
Certain features of our Services, such as our mobile apps or educational tools, may require access to your device’s location or address book. You can manage these permissions through your device settings. Disabling these features may limit the functionality of certain aspects of the Services.

*Cookies*
Most browsers accept cookies by default, but you can modify your browser settings to reject cookies. However, doing so may affect your ability to use certain features of our Services, including access to specific educational content.

*Promotional Messages*
You can opt out of receiving promotional messages from us by following the instructions included in those messages or by updating your preferences in your account settings. However, even if you opt out, we may still send you non-promotional communications related to your account, such as notifications about your course progress or our ongoing business dealings.

*Push Notifications*
With your consent, we may send push notifications to your mobile device. You can disable these notifications at any time through your device settings.

### Agreement

This Privacy Policy, along with our Terms of Use and other related policies, constitutes the entire agreement between you and MoneyWave regarding the use of our Services. We reserve the right to modify this policy at any time, and we encourage you to review it regularly to stay informed of any changes.

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us through the details provided on our website.

_Last Updated: [01.01.2005]''';

